00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:39.480
from like a few years
ago that essentially

00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:40.910
is sort of doing exactly that.

00:05:40.910 --> 00:05:43.370
I just want to sort of flag
this so you're not surprised.

00:05:43.370 --> 00:05:47.240
This is essentially
sort of 1401 basics

00:05:47.240 --> 00:05:49.100
that we discussed in
the first recitation.

00:05:49.100 --> 00:05:52.760
There's also some handout
on some refreshers for that,

00:05:52.760 --> 00:05:54.270
but that'll come as well.

00:05:54.270 --> 00:05:55.820
But the same
principles apply here.

00:05:55.820 --> 00:05:59.600
That's exactly the same thing as
